group
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,785,971]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
The 
<taxonomicName box="[203,349,785,811]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Ischnopoderona" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gracilicornis">gracilicornis</taxonomicName>
group is characterized by the following combination of characters: the pronotal puncturation much finer anteriorly than that posteriorly, the pronotal pubescence at midline directed posteriorly in apical 
<number box="[1413,1424,825,851]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[151,166,865,891]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="4.0">4</number>
and anteriorly in basal ¾, the pronotal pubescence at postero­lateral parts directed straight anteriorly (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 4 – 11" captionStartId="9.[151,269,1603,1627]" captionTargetBox="[303,1284,194,1585]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[295,1291,183,1592]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 4 – 11. Ischnopoderona gracilicornis (Scheerp.): 4 — maxilla, 5 — labium, 6 — right mandible, 7 — labrum, 8 — mentum, 9 — shape of elytron, 10 — pronotal pubescence, 11 — tergite VIII." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/175637/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
Fig. 
<number box="[151,168,905,931]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="9.0">9</number>
</figureCitation>
), the pronotal basal impression small and shallow, weakly visible and the posterior margin of tergite VIII with row of apical spines.
</paragraph>
